Covered employment (excludes federal gov:
NOTES: Except where noted, excludes data for federal employees and for ex-servicemembers; includes data for state and local government employees where covered by state law after 1955.
          Totals do not necessarily equal the sum of rounded components.
Insured unemployment as percent of cover: a. Total wages earned in covered employment during all pay periods ended within the year.
Number of first payments: b. Based on average covered employment in 12-month period.
Average weekly benefit for total unemplo: c. Includes dependents' allowances for states that provide such benefits.
Average weekly insured unemployment: d. Based on average total weekly wage in current year.
Average actual duration (weeks): e. Percentages based on first payments for 12-month period.
Claimants exhausting benefits: f. Contributions, penalties, and interest from employers and contributions from employees in states taxing workers; adjusted to exclude refunds of contributions and dishonored checks; excludes state and local government employees covered on reimbursable basis.
Contributions collected f (millions of d: g. Adjusted to exclude voided benefit checks and for transfers under interstate combined-wage plan; excludes Extended Benefits and Emergency Unemployment Compensation.
Benefits paid g (millions of dollars): h. Estimated data. Contribution rate as a percentage of taxable payroll; excludes state and local jurisdictions covering state and local government employees on a reimbursable basis. Standard contribution rate for most states, 2.7 percent.
